Basic command line options

-b --bare               Show unformatted report
-c --category <name>    categorise/tag your expenses
-e --earned             indicates income
-f --file <name>        specify file name

-s [n]                  show daily report with total after [n] days
-m [n]                  monthly report with total after [n] months
-C                      show category/tag-wise report
-t --total              shows just the total when used with -s

-M <mm>                 select the start month (01 <= mm <= 12)
-N <mm>                 select and end month (01 <= mm <= 12)
-Y <yy>                 select a year (00 <= yy <= 99)

-h --help               show this help
-v --version            show version

#################################################################
Report mode
----------
-b, --bare : show unformatted report
-c, --category : categorise/tag your expenses
-e, --earned: indicates income
-f, --file: specify file to be used by pem
-s [n] : show daily report with total after [n] days
-m [n] : show monthly report with total after [n] months
-C : show category/tag-wise report
-t, --total: show just the total when used with -s
-M <mm> : select the start month (01 <= mm <= 12)
-N <mm> : select an end month (01 <= mm <= 12)
-Y <yy> : select a year (00 <= yy << 99)
-h, --help : show this help
-v, --version: show version information

----------- Design note
Input data or record:
 - designation of the expenditure : string
 - expense : float
 - tag : string
record-stamp:
 - date
 - time

